<%# src/views/partials/special-lucky-option.ejs
    Issue #650: the "Lucky task" option in the Special radio, plus the
    accordion panel that opens under it when it is picked.

    Sibling of special-oneday-option.ejs in the same .special-option-group
    shape (that partial's own header names #650 as one of the two siblings to
    come). ONE partial, included by BOTH task-create-dialog.ejs (step 2) and
    task-edit-dialog.ejs, so the create flow and the edit popup cannot drift.

    The panel is shown by CSS alone (.special-option-group:has(input:checked)),
    like every other option in the group.

    Locals:
      idPrefix   — 'task-create' | 'task-edit'; keeps element ids unique when
                   both dialogs are on the same page.
      eventDays  — REQUIRED, [{ iso, label }] from the #681 Configuration
                   page's wedding dates, same local special-oneday-option.ejs
                   reads. No fallback, deliberately.

    No selection state lives in this partial; create defaults and edit state
    come from src/public/js/admin-tasks.js, same as the one-day option.
%>
<div class="special-option-group">
  <label class="special-option">
    <input type="radio" name="special_mode" value="lucky" />
    <span class="special-option-face">
      <span class="special-option-title">Lucky task</span>
      <span class="special-option-sub">A secret bonus on one day &mdash; guests find out only after they post</span>
    </span>
  </label>

  <div class="special-panel">
    <div class="special-panel-field">
      <span class="field-label" id="<%= idPrefix %>-lucky-day-label">Which day</span>
      <div class="day-chips" role="radiogroup" aria-labelledby="<%= idPrefix %>-lucky-day-label">
        <% eventDays.forEach(function (d) { %>
          <label class="worth-chip day-chip">
            <input type="radio" name="lucky_date" value="<%= d.iso %>" />
            <span class="worth-chip-face"><%= d.label %></span>
          </label>
        <% }); %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="special-panel-field">
      <span class="field-label" id="<%= idPrefix %>-lucky-bonus-label">Secret bonus</span>
      <div class="worth-chips" role="radiogroup" aria-labelledby="<%= idPrefix %>-lucky-bonus-label">
        <% [1, 2, 3].forEach(function (n) { %>
          <label class="worth-chip">
            <input type="radio" name="lucky_bonus" value="<%= n %>" />
            <span class="worth-chip-face">+<%= n %> pt<%= n === 1 ? '' : 's' %></span>
          </label>
        <% }); %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <% if (idPrefix === 'task-edit') { %>
      <%# Carries a stored lucky_date that matches no rendered day chip
          (issue #650) -- the same stale-date pattern task-edit-dialog.ejs
          uses for special_date, but living HERE (not in that file) so this
          partial stays the single owner of every lucky field, per the
          issue's plan step 6. Disabled by default so it posts nothing;
          admin-tasks.js's openEdit() enables it and sets its value only for
          such a task, and disables it again the moment any lucky day chip
          above is clicked, so the chips stay the only source of lucky_date
          whenever one matches and the body never carries two values for that
          field. Renders nothing visible, so it changes no approved pixel —
          absent from the CREATE dialog, which has no stored date to carry. %>
      <input type="hidden" name="lucky_date" id="task-edit-lucky-date-stale" disabled />
    <% } %>
  </div>
</div>
